'''[[Cannabis]] in [[Kenya]]''' is illegal; the drug is locally referred to as '''bhang''' or '''banghi'''.<ref name="Daly1996">{{cite book|author=Paul V. Daly|title=The Supply of Illicit Drugs to the United States: The Nnicc Report|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LvbJsQgnlXwC&pg=PA64|date=July 1996|publisher=DIANE Publishing|isbn=978-0-7881-3942-0|pages=64–}}</ref>

==History==
Cannabis ("bhang") was banned in Kenya during the British colonial [[East Africa Protectorate]] under the Opium Ordinance, effective 1 January 1914.<ref>{{cite book|title=Kenya Gazette|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-tucX8G18BkC&pg=PA882|date=15 October 1913|pages=882–}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Kenya Gazette|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MmQ16P1RMmAC&pg=PA203|date=4 March 1914|pages=203–}}</ref>

